<div class = "row flex-lg-row-reverse align-items-center g-5 py-4 mb-4">
    <div class = "col-12 col-lg-6">
        <img src = "/img/people eating.jpeg" width = "670" height="510" class = "d-block mx-lg-auto img-fluid" Loading ="lazy" alt = "cooking recipes">
    </div>


    <div class = "col-12 col-lg-6"> 
         <h1 class = "display-5 fw-bold mb-3 justify-content-left"> EXPLORE VARIOUS VARIETIES OF RECIPES </h1>
         <p class = "lead text-justify">
            Delving into the world of culinary creations is akin to composing a symphony for the senses. Recipes, the poetic scripts of gastronomy, beckon us into a realm where ingredients dance harmoniously, and flavors unfold like well-rehearsed melodies. Within the elegant embrace of a recipe, each measured step is a note, carefully composed to orchestrate a masterpiece on the palate.

            In the artistry of gastronomy, a recipe is a canvas awaiting the stroke of a culinary brush. It weaves tales of tradition, transcending time and cultural boundaries, while inviting the adept and the novice alike to participate in the timeless ritual of preparing a meal. It transforms ordinary moments into extraordinary experiences, as the alchemy of ingredients melds and metamorphoses into something greater than the sum of its parts.

            A recipe is not merely a list of instructions; it is an ode to exploration, an invitation to embark on a journey of flavors. It whispers secrets of balance, coaxing out the nuances of each component, and encourages the creator to infuse the dish with a personal touch. The act of following a recipe becomes a ritual of connection, linking us to generations past and to the global tapestry of culinary heritage.


         </p>

         <div class = "d-grid gap-2 d-md-flex justify-content-md-start">
            <a href = "/explore-latest" class = "btn btn-primary btn-dark btn-lg px-4 me-md-2"> Explore Latest</a>
            <a href = "/explore-random" class = "btn btn-outline-secondary  btn-lg px-4 me-md-2"> Explore Random ones </a>
         </div>
    </div>
</div>


<!-- categories start -->
<div class = "row row-cols-2 row-cols-lg-6 g-2 g-log-3 py-4">

    

     <% if(categories != '') { %>
        <% categories.forEach(function(category, index) {  %>
    <a href = "/categories/<%- category.name %>" class = "col text-center category__link">
        <div class = "category__img shadow">
            <img src = "img/<%- category.image %>" alt = "<%- category.name %>" Loading = "Lazy">
        </div>
        <div class = "pt-1"> <%- category.name %> </div>
    </a>
    <% }) %>
    <% } %>

    

    <a href = "/categories" class = "col text-center category__link">
        <div class = "category__img shadow">
            <img src = "img/american recipes.jpg" alt = "view other all catgories  " Loading = "Lazy">
        </div>
        <div class = "pt-1"> view all  </div>
    </a>

   
</div>




<!-- categories end -->


